 why Sadhana. To\n&gt; slowly g=\r\nnaw away at my own mind, to be better able to appreciate this\n&gt; endless, na=\r\nmeless entity. G_d.\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; I do not believe in Moksha. What is Moksha? No re=\r\nbirth? If the Universe\n&gt; itself gets born over and over and over, if Rama a=\r\nnd Krshna come back at\n&gt; every cycle, who am I to demand that I should not =\r\nget born? Infact, when a\n&gt; person proverbially finishes off his/her karmas,=\r\n they merely go to another\n&gt; plane in this Universe and stay there for eons=\r\n of time, since time anyway\n&gt; moves very, very slowly in different realms. =\r\nBut then, if this force so\n&gt; wants, it can send back any of the souls from =\r\nany of the realms to any of\n&gt; the other realms to serve a certain function.=\r\n And if a soul stays in a\n&gt; certain higher realm and in forced to take rebi=\r\nrth again, the seeds of the\n&gt; karmas - which never really die off - are  wa=\r\ntered again by the environment\n&gt; of birth and they sprout into saplings. An=\r\nd this may go even beyond one\n&gt; cycle of creation. Else why would Krshna an=\r\nd Arjuna fight the very same\n&gt; enemies that they had been fighting in the p=\r\nast cycle of creation?\n&gt; Mahabharata says so. I believe it.\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; What th=\r\nen is the final aim of all this, spirituality etc? I don&#39;t know.\n&gt; Maybe, t=\r\no teach us to broaden our perspectives and consequentially lessen\n&gt; our att=\r\nachments to our otherwise mundane lives and its mundane problems.\n&gt; This is=\r\n like a circular roller-coaster ride we see in local melas. Tighten\n&gt; the s=\r\neat-belts, bring a smile in the heart, be detached and enjoy the show!\n&gt;\n&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; Best of luck and take good care of yourself!\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; -Regards\n&gt;  Rajarshi\n&gt;=\r\n\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; *awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah | *\n&gt; *param bhAwamaj=\r\nAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24] *\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&