this tale? &gt;&gt; &lt;font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; =\r\ncolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#0000=\r\n00&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I will tell you how I see it. In this story, God means=\r\n infinity. Now what is infinity? It cannot be described, it cannot be named=\r\n, it cannot be understood using the five sense organs. Science does not und=\r\nerstand infinity, art\n does not understand infinity, nothing or nobody=A0 u=\r\nnderstands infinity. It is a summation of all that we know, all that we can=\r\n=A0 imagine and all that is impossible for us to imagine. It is an incompre=\r\nhensible force that runs through everything, from the most loveable to the =\r\nmost despicable , from the most holy to the most unholy, from the greatest =\r\nsaint to the stupidest piece of rock at the bottom of the deepest ocean in =\r\nthe farthest planet in the farthest solar system in the farthest universe. =\r\n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font si=\r\nze=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#0000=\r\n00&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Now question is, can an average human being &=\r\nquot;know&quot; this mysterious and all pervading force? Knowing implies un=\r\nderstanding. Clearly no. Then how does one interact with such a thing? One =\r\nway is to consider\n everything, and I mean EVERYTHING from living to non-li=\r\nving, as a manifestation of that force and thus learn to love the same unco=\r\nnditionally without expecting anything in return. No wonder such unconditio=\r\nnal love is not easy. It needs tremendous effort to change our own conditio=\r\nning of the mind, and work on our inherent biases and prejudices. That is w=\r\nhat the=A0 aim of sadhana is, in my view. To work on oneself, to make one r=\r\neady to be able to unconditionally love everything. The greater number of e=\r\nntities one can love unconditionally, that much little bit closer one can c=\r\nome to interacting with the truly infinite. And those few rare human beings=\r\n who can love a whole universe unconditionally, are possibly the closest to=\r\n this supreme and unknowable force. In common language, we call them Rishis=\r\n. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/=\r\nfont&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana=\r\n&quot;&gt;I like all forms of\n Deities, for I find something beautiful in everyone =\r\nof them. And I also like the One behind forms, which is so perfectly transc=\r\nendental that it cannot be comprehended ever. It&#39;s like the surface are=\r\na of the fine tip of a needle, or the gap between the two breaths, or the m=\r\nillionth part of a single hair, or the endless-ness of space, or the bottom=\r\nless well of stillness in the mind at certain points in meditation. The onl=\r\ny thing that stops me from getting a better understanding the grandeur of=\r\n=A0 this formless entity are the limitations of my own mind and body, that =\r\nI have acquired over millions of births. That is why Sadhana. To slowly gna=\r\nw away at my own mind, to be better able to appreciate this endless, namele=\r\nss entity. G_d. &lt;font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#0000=\r\n00&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&